WEBVTT

1
00:00:20.625 --> 00:00:23.125
DOWNFALL

2
00:00:24.125 --> 00:00:29.625
I feel as if I should be angry
with that child. that...

3
00:00:30.125 --> 00:00:34.125
naive young girl.
Or that I must not forgive her...

4
00:00:34.625 --> 00:00:38.125
for not recognising the
nature of that monster.

5
00:00:39.125 --> 00:00:41.925
For not being aware of what
she was getting into.

6
00:00:42.425 --> 00:00:45.925
And especially that I went
along without thinking.

7
00:00:46.425 --> 00:00:52.425
Because I wasn't a fanatical Nazi.
I could have said. in Berlin:

8
00:00:52.426 --> 00:00:56.925
'No. I'm not doing it. I don't want
to go to the Führer's headquarters.'

9
00:00:57.925 --> 00:01:00.926
But I didn't do that.
I was too curious.

10
00:01:01.426 --> 00:01:04.426
I also didn't realise...

11
00:01:05.426 --> 00:01:10.426
that destiny would take me somewhere
I didn't want to be.

12
00:01:11.426 --> 00:01:16.926
But. nevertheless. I find it hard
to forgive myself.

13
00:01:22.750 --> 00:01:23.750
The ladies are here.

14
00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:29.250
It's confirmed.
-They can pass.

15
00:01:57.128 --> 00:02:00.128
'Wolfsschanze'
headquarters of the Führer

16
00:02:01.128 --> 00:02:02.628
November 1942
Rastenburg. East-Prussia

17
00:02:06.128 --> 00:02:08.128
Sit down. ladies.

18
00:02:09.628 --> 00:02:14.628
One moment. The Führer is feeding
his dog. He'll see you in a short while.

19
00:02:16.628 --> 00:02:21.128
Can you tell us... How are we supposed
to address the Führer?

20
00:02:22.128 --> 00:02:26.128
The Führer first speaks to you
and then you reply: Heil. mein Führer.

21
00:02:26.129 --> 00:02:28.128
And the Nazi salute?

22
00:02:28.129 --> 00:02:30.628
That won't be necessary...

23
00:02:30.629 --> 00:02:35.628
since the Führer isn't looking for
a soldier. but for a secretary.

24
00:02:36.128 --> 00:02:38.628
Act as normal and relaxed
as you can.

25
00:02:39.628 --> 00:02:41.628
I'll see if
if he has time for you.

26
00:02:45.628 --> 00:02:48.628
Mein Führer.
the ladies from Berlin are here.

27
00:03:06.634 --> 00:03:12.134
Thank you for coming
in the middle of the night.

28
00:03:12.634 --> 00:03:17.134
Sometimes. during a war.
one is not in control of time.

29
00:03:19.058 --> 00:03:22.558
Can I ask your name?
-Margarethe Lorenz.

30
00:03:23.058 --> 00:03:25.558
Where are you from?
-From Fulda.

31
00:03:26.058 --> 00:03:29.558
And what is your name?
-Ursula Puttkammer. Heil. mein Führer.

32
00:03:30.058 --> 00:03:33.058
No need for that.
Where are you from?

33
00:03:33.558 --> 00:03:35.558
Frankfurt am Main. mein Füh...

34
00:03:37.558 --> 00:03:39.558
Hannah Potrovsky.
born and raised in Berlin.

35
00:03:40.558 --> 00:03:42.558
In Pankow. to be precise.

36
00:03:43.558 --> 00:03:46.058
Hedwig Brandt
from Crailsheim. Schwaben.

37
00:03:47.558 --> 00:03:51.058
And you are?
-Traudl Humps. I'm from Munich.

38
00:03:54.058 --> 00:03:55.558
A lady from Munich.

39
00:04:02.558 --> 00:04:06.058
Shall we start then.
Fräulein Humps?

40
00:04:16.558 --> 00:04:20.058
My Blondi won't hurt you.
She's very intelligent.

41
00:04:20.558 --> 00:04:24.058
She's much smarter
than most people.

42
00:04:28.557 --> 00:04:31.557
First. sit down. please.

43
00:04:32.057 --> 00:04:36.057
Don't be nervous. I make
many mistakes during dictation.

44
00:04:36.058 --> 00:04:39.557
You won't make nearly as many.

45
00:04:48.557 --> 00:04:50.057
You're very young.

46
00:04:50.058 --> 00:04:55.058
How old are you?
-22. mein Führer.

47
00:04:59.558 --> 00:05:03.558
My German fellow-countrymen
and women...

48
00:05:04.558 --> 00:05:05.558
...fellow party members.

49
00:05:05.559 --> 00:05:10.058
It is. I think. rather special...

50
00:05:10.558 --> 00:05:16.558
that. after 20 years of service. a man still
stands in front of his supporters...

51
00:05:19.558 --> 00:05:26.058
...and that in all those 20 years. his program
never needed to be modified.

52
00:05:40.558 --> 00:05:44.058
I suggest we try it again.

53
00:05:55.831 --> 00:05:57.831
I did it.
He hired me.

54
00:06:13.831 --> 00:06:16.331
Berlin - 20 April 1945
Hitler's 56th birthday

55
00:06:16.831 --> 00:06:18.331
two and a half years later

56
00:06:18.831 --> 00:06:19.831
Take cover.

57
00:06:24.281 --> 00:06:27.781
Hurry. Continue.
Get that off the street.

58
00:06:30.058 --> 00:06:31.058
Take cover.

59
00:06:43.644 --> 00:06:44.644
That's artillery fire.

60
00:06:45.144 --> 00:06:49.144
Don't be silly.
Where would it be coming from?

61
00:06:49.644 --> 00:06:52.144
You're right. These are no planes.
this is artillery.

62
00:06:53.144 --> 00:06:57.644
It's the Russians.
What a birthday present.

63
00:07:01.644 --> 00:07:03.644
Where is that cannon fire coming from?

64
00:07:04.144 --> 00:07:06.644
Happy Birthday.
mein Führer.

65
00:07:07.144 --> 00:07:09.144
The city centre of Berlin
is under fire.

66
00:07:10.323 --> 00:07:13.822
Grenades have hit near the Brandenburger
Tor and the Reichstag.

67
00:07:14.143 --> 00:07:16.643
Where did they come from?
-We don't know yet.

68
00:07:17.143 --> 00:07:20.143
I have Koller on the line.
-Give me Koller.

69
00:07:20.643 --> 00:07:24.643
Koller. do you know Berlin
is under artillery fire?

70
00:07:25.643 --> 00:07:28.143
No.
-Can't you hear the shooting?

71
00:07:28.643 --> 00:07:31.643
No. I'm in Wildpark-Werder.
-Berlin is chaotic.

72
00:07:32.143 --> 00:07:34.643
Apparently. the Russians captured
a railway bridge over the Oder.

73
00:07:35.643 --> 00:07:38.643
The enemy has no railway
artillery near the Oder.

74
00:07:39.143 --> 00:07:41.143
It's not long-range artillery.

75
00:07:41.144 --> 00:07:46.143
The anti-aircraft defence near the Zoo-Bunker
reports they're 10 to 12...

76
00:07:46.144 --> 00:07:50.643
... cm calibres. The Russians have
positions near Marzahn.

77
00:07:50.644 --> 00:07:55.143
That's only 12 kilometres from the centre.
Are the Russians that close?

78
00:07:55.643 --> 00:07:59.143
They should hang the entire
Luftwaffe leadership.

79
00:08:00.617 --> 00:08:03.117
This is unheard-of.

80
00:08:03.643 --> 00:08:06.143
The Russians are at 12 kilometres
from the city centre.

81
00:08:07.143 --> 00:08:09.643
Nobody told me anything.
I had to ask.

82
00:08:10.643 --> 00:08:13.143
Maybe it's long-range artillery.
after all.

83
00:08:13.643 --> 00:08:16.643
That railway bridge over the Oder...
-Nonsense.

84
00:08:22.643 --> 00:08:25.143
That Himmler.
such a pompous buffoon.

85
00:08:25.643 --> 00:08:31.143
Party bosses. everywhere.
They make me so sick.

86
00:08:33.643 --> 00:08:35.643
The Führer starts
'Clausewitz' today.

87
00:08:36.643 --> 00:08:40.143
Berlin as a front city.
He won't be able to keep the city.

88
00:08:40.643 --> 00:08:43.643
If the Führer stays here.
the Reich will go down with him.

89
00:08:44.143 --> 00:08:47.643
We have to talk him out of it.
Talk to Hewel.

90
00:08:47.644 --> 00:08:51.143
He's the only diplomat
with any influence on him.

91
00:08:51.643 --> 00:08:54.643
Hewel tried everything.
It's useless.

92
00:08:55.143 --> 00:08:57.643
Talk to your sister-in-law. then.

93
00:08:58.143 --> 00:09:03.143
Why not? You're married
to the sister of Eva Braun.

94
00:09:03.643 --> 00:09:07.143
We must try everything.
Berlin is almost surrounded.

95
00:09:07.144 --> 00:09:10.143
You're still young.
You'll be a father soon.

96
00:09:10.643 --> 00:09:13.143
Do you want to die here?
-Absolutely not.

97
00:09:18.143 --> 00:09:20.143
Gentlemen. the Führer.

98
00:09:30.571 --> 00:09:34.071
Everything out. Quickly.
We're leaving in two hours.

99
00:09:41.913 --> 00:09:44.913
What's going on?
-We're leaving.

100
00:09:46.913 --> 00:09:48.413
'Clausewitz' has started.

101
00:09:48.838 --> 00:09:52.338
All the ministries and departments
are leaving Berlin.

102
00:09:52.913 --> 00:09:55.913
And who's going to look after
the people and the soldiers?

103
00:09:56.912 --> 00:10:00.412
Don't ask me. professor.
-This is insane.

104
00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:19.450
Professor.

105
00:10:20.450 --> 00:10:22.450
I won't allow the
evacuation of my office.

106
00:10:22.950 --> 00:10:26.950
Is that so?
-Food supply would collapse.

107
00:10:27.450 --> 00:10:29.950
A good soldier can
always find food.

108
00:10:30.450 --> 00:10:34.950
And when there's fighting all over the city.
where does he get it? The population.

109
00:10:35.800 --> 00:10:38.800
It's irresponsible.
-It's an order from the Führer.

110
00:10:40.301 --> 00:10:43.301
As department head. I
report to the SS and to Himmler.

111
00:10:43.801 --> 00:10:47.801
But as a doctor. I'm part of the Wehrmacht
and they're not leaving yet.

112
00:10:48.301 --> 00:10:50.801
Keep that in mind.

113
00:10:55.301 --> 00:10:58.801
The professor stays in Berlin.
Get him the proper papers.

114
00:11:02.229 --> 00:11:03.729
We're leaving.

115
00:11:16.758 --> 00:11:19.258
Everything for Germany.
Heil. mein Führer.

116
00:11:20.758 --> 00:11:23.258
Führer. I...
Heil. mein Führer.

117
00:11:24.643 --> 00:11:27.143
They're in such a hurry
to get away from here.

118
00:11:27.643 --> 00:11:29.643
The brown nosing is the worst.

119
00:11:30.143 --> 00:11:33.643
They say 'Sieg Heil'. but they think
'Lick my... you know what.'

120
00:11:37.567 --> 00:11:42.067
Mein Führer. I beg you: Leave Berlin.
It is not too late yet.

121
00:11:43.067 --> 00:11:44.567
Too late?

122
00:11:46.067 --> 00:11:48.067
Hewel. come here for a moment.

123
00:11:48.674 --> 00:11:53.174
I'm sure you agree we should contact
the Allies...

124
00:11:53.674 --> 00:11:58.674
...and start conducting politics.
-Certainly. We need politics.

125
00:11:58.675 --> 00:12:02.674
Politics?
I don't do politics anymore.

126
00:12:02.675 --> 00:12:05.174
I'm fed up with it.

127
00:12:07.174 --> 00:12:11.174
When I'm dead. you'll have plenty
of time for politics.

128
00:12:11.674 --> 00:12:17.318
It's good. dear Himmler.
My loyal Heinrich.

129
00:12:17.319 --> 00:12:22.064
It's good.
Just go.

130
00:12:41.602 --> 00:12:43.102
He has no strength left.

131
00:12:44.102 --> 00:12:47.602
What did you expect from a
vegetarian teetotaller?

132
00:12:48.102 --> 00:12:51.602
Seriously. though. Fegelein.
I'm taking control now.

133
00:12:52.602 --> 00:12:54.602
Berlin will fall in a couple of days.

134
00:12:55.102 --> 00:12:59.602
When the Führer's dead. who will
the Allies negotiate with?

135
00:12:59.603 --> 00:13:02.602
Why do you think they'll
negotiate with you?

136
00:13:03.102 --> 00:13:06.102
The Nazi state and my SS are needed
to maintain order.

137
00:13:07.102 --> 00:13:09.102
One hour with Eisenhower
and he'll feel the same way.

138
00:13:10.102 --> 00:13:14.102
The first contact has been made.
-Careful. that's high treason.

139
00:13:14.602 --> 00:13:17.102
Fegelein. I have other concerns.

140
00:13:17.103 --> 00:13:22.102
Should I give Eisenhower the Nazi salute
or shake his hand?

141
00:13:28.445 --> 00:13:29.945
Look at that.

142
00:13:32.945 --> 00:13:34.445
The best guests
always arrive late.

143
00:13:34.945 --> 00:13:39.945
Leaving already. gentlemen?
I wanted to talk to you.

144
00:13:40.445 --> 00:13:44.945
The scorched-earth order...
-I really have to go now.

145
00:13:44.946 --> 00:13:47.945
Come and see me one day
in Hohenlychen.

146
00:13:50.445 --> 00:13:55.445
I'm going north to help with the
battle of Berlin there.

147
00:14:04.949 --> 00:14:09.449
You know. Speer... There's an
advantage to those bombings.

148
00:14:09.949 --> 00:14:14.949
It's easier to clean up debris
than to demolish everything ourselves.

149
00:14:16.449 --> 00:14:19.949
When the war will be over.
reconstruction will be quick.

150
00:14:21.449 --> 00:14:26.949
We spent thousands of hours
together with these replicas.

151
00:14:28.449 --> 00:14:31.449
You're a true genius. Speer.

152
00:14:32.949 --> 00:14:38.449
Yes. absolutely. Only you and I know
that the Third Reich would be inconceivable...

153
00:14:38.949 --> 00:14:43.449
...with only warehouses and factories.
Skyscrapers and hotels.

154
00:14:44.449 --> 00:14:48.449
This Third Reich will be a treasury
full of art and culture...

155
00:14:48.949 --> 00:14:51.949
...that will survive thousands of years.

156
00:14:51.950 --> 00:14:56.250
We see. before us. the ancient cities.
the Acropolis...

157
00:14:56.750 --> 00:14:59.250
We see the medieval cities...
the cathedrals...

158
00:14:59.251 --> 00:15:03.750
...and we know that the people
need that.

159
00:15:06.750 --> 00:15:09.250
Indeed. Speer.

160
00:15:11.750 --> 00:15:13.750
That was my vision...

161
00:15:15.250 --> 00:15:17.750
...and it still is.

162
00:15:20.250 --> 00:15:25.250
Mein Führer. if you want to realize
these plans. you must leave Berlin.

163
00:15:30.749 --> 00:15:33.249
Eva. you say something.

164
00:15:33.749 --> 00:15:36.749
He's the Führer.
He knows what's best.

165
00:15:37.249 --> 00:15:41.749
You must leave Berlin.
The Russians almost have us isolated.

166
00:15:42.249 --> 00:15:44.249
I can't do that. my child.

167
00:15:44.749 --> 00:15:49.749
I would be like a lama priest
with an empty prayer wheel.

168
00:15:49.750 --> 00:15:55.526
I have to solve the problem.
here in Berlin. or perish.

169
00:15:57.026 --> 00:15:58.026
Speer...

170
00:16:00.526 --> 00:16:02.026
...what do you think?

171
00:16:03.526 --> 00:16:06.526
You have to be on the stage
when the curtain falls.

172
00:16:24.117 --> 00:16:25.117
Reload.

173
00:16:35.260 --> 00:16:37.260
Go away. Leave me alone.

174
00:16:37.760 --> 00:16:41.260
How old are you? Twelve?
And you? Fourteen?

175
00:16:41.760 --> 00:16:44.760
Why are you here?
To play at war? Go home.

176
00:16:45.260 --> 00:16:48.760
Who are you? What do you want?
I want my son. Alive.

177
00:16:49.260 --> 00:16:52.260
You should be proud.
He destroyed two tanks.

178
00:16:52.760 --> 00:16:55.760
The Führer will decorate him
for it. today.

179
00:16:56.260 --> 00:16:59.260
You're still young.
At which front did you fight?

180
00:17:00.260 --> 00:17:01.760
I haven't had
the honour yet.

181
00:17:02.260 --> 00:17:06.760
Count yourself lucky.
Send the children home.

182
00:17:07.760 --> 00:17:09.760
We'll defend this position
to the last man.

183
00:17:10.260 --> 00:17:13.260
Which position?
This is not a position. it's a trap.

184
00:17:14.260 --> 00:17:17.260
The Russians will come from two sides
and you won't be able to get out.

185
00:17:17.760 --> 00:17:19.760
We'll shoot back.
-What with?

186
00:17:20.760 --> 00:17:22.260
With the anti-aircraft guns.

187
00:17:22.760 --> 00:17:26.260
The Russians will arrive with several
armies. tanks and heavy artillery.

188
00:17:26.760 --> 00:17:30.760
Do you really think you'll
last even five minutes?

189
00:17:31.260 --> 00:17:33.760
We promised the Führer.

190
00:17:34.260 --> 00:17:37.260
Don't you understand?
The war is lost.

191
00:17:37.760 --> 00:17:38.760
Coward.

192
00:17:43.260 --> 00:17:45.260
Go away. Right now.

193
00:17:46.760 --> 00:17:50.760
If you're still here when the Russians
arrive. you'll all be dead.

194
00:17:54.260 --> 00:17:59.760
The 9th army had to retreat
or they would have been decimated...

195
00:18:00.260 --> 00:18:05.260
We won't retreat the 9th army.
Busse must fight where he stands.

196
00:18:05.760 --> 00:18:08.260
Führer. then the 9th army is lost.

197
00:18:08.760 --> 00:18:13.759
We'll push back the Soviet armies
in the north and east...

198
00:18:13.760 --> 00:18:18.259
...with a ruthless. mighty attack.

199
00:18:19.259 --> 00:18:20.259
Using which units?

200
00:18:21.259 --> 00:18:25.759
Steiner will attack from the north
and join the 9th army.

201
00:18:27.759 --> 00:18:30.259
The 9th army is unable to move.

202
00:18:30.759 --> 00:18:32.759
The enemy outnumbers us ten times.

203
00:18:33.759 --> 00:18:36.259
Wenck's 12th army must
support them.

204
00:18:36.759 --> 00:18:41.759
The 12th army is approaching the Elbe.
-Then it must turn around.

205
00:18:42.259 --> 00:18:46.259
Then the western front would be open.
-Do you doubt my orders?

206
00:18:46.759 --> 00:18:50.259
I think I've been
clear enough.

207
00:18:51.759 --> 00:18:58.759
The Allies will see that only we
can stop the Bolsheviks.

208
00:18:59.259 --> 00:19:03.759
We have to keep Berlin and
make a deal with the Americans.

209
00:19:22.259 --> 00:19:25.259
Mohnke. you're here.
-Mein Führer.

210
00:19:26.759 --> 00:19:31.259
Today. 'Clausewitz' started.
Berlin will be a front city.

211
00:19:31.759 --> 00:19:36.259
You will be the commander of the
defensive circle around the citadel.

212
00:19:36.759 --> 00:19:40.759
We'll fight until the last man. in Berlin.

213
00:19:41.259 --> 00:19:45.259
There are still three million civilians here.
They have to be evacuated.

214
00:19:46.759 --> 00:19:52.759
I understand your concern. Mohnke.
But we have to be cold as ice.

215
00:19:53.259 --> 00:19:56.759
We can't spend any energy
on so-called civilians.

216
00:19:58.259 --> 00:20:02.259
With all due respect. what will
happen to the women and children...

217
00:20:02.759 --> 00:20:05.259
...and the thousands of wounded
and elderly?

218
00:20:05.759 --> 00:20:09.259
In a war such as this one.
there are no civilians.

219
00:20:10.259 --> 00:20:12.259
The Führer has lost all
sense of reality.

220
00:20:12.759 --> 00:20:15.759
He's moving divisions around
that no longer exist.

221
00:20:16.259 --> 00:20:21.259
Gruppe Steiner has been scattered.
yet Steiner must attack. Madness.

222
00:20:21.759 --> 00:20:25.259
But why don't you tell him that?
-He doesn't listen to reason.

223
00:20:25.759 --> 00:20:29.759
Something has to happen.
-Are you crazy? He'll throw us out.

224
00:20:32.259 --> 00:20:35.759
We're soldiers.
We took an oath.

225
00:20:35.760 --> 00:20:38.259
Does that mean we can't use
our own brains anymore?

226
00:20:38.759 --> 00:20:41.759
And that's coming from you?
A ruthless careerist?

227
00:20:42.759 --> 00:20:43.759
I beg your pardon?

228
00:21:07.920 --> 00:21:09.920
Where were you?
-None of your business.

229
00:21:18.493 --> 00:21:22.493
The most successful tank hunters of the
Berlin Hitler-Jugend stand before you.

230
00:21:31.452 --> 00:21:32.452
I'm proud of you.

231
00:21:35.952 --> 00:21:39.952
This boy took out two tanks
using anti-tank shells.

232
00:21:40.452 --> 00:21:44.952
His name is Peter Kranz.
-So you're Peter.

233
00:21:46.952 --> 00:21:50.452
I wish my generals were
as brave as you.

234
00:21:59.946 --> 00:22:00.946
Very good.

235
00:22:07.218 --> 00:22:09.218
You've made history.

236
00:22:09.718 --> 00:22:14.218
And when Germania will rise
from these ruins...

237
00:22:14.718 --> 00:22:16.718
...you will be the heroes.

238
00:22:18.218 --> 00:22:20.218
Heil. to you.

239
00:22:48.713 --> 00:22:52.713
I don't know about you.
but I prefer air raids.

240
00:22:53.713 --> 00:22:58.213
What will happen to us?
-I could go if I wanted to.

241
00:22:58.713 --> 00:23:03.213
But everybody is deserting him.
We can't all go. can we?

242
00:23:03.713 --> 00:23:05.213
I can't go either.

243
00:23:10.713 --> 00:23:13.213
I wouldn't know
where to go.

244
00:23:13.713 --> 00:23:18.213
My parents and all
my friends warned me.

245
00:23:18.713 --> 00:23:21.213
Don't get involved with the Nazis.

246
00:23:21.713 --> 00:23:24.713
What should I say:
'Hello. I made a mistake'?

247
00:23:24.714 --> 00:23:27.213
'When things went wrong.
I admitted my mistake.'

248
00:23:29.213 --> 00:23:31.713
Life will go on.

249
00:23:39.823 --> 00:23:42.823
What do you think. Herr Oberst?
-We have to go.

250
00:23:45.823 --> 00:23:48.823
Go where?
-I don't know.

251
00:23:49.323 --> 00:23:51.323
Wherever they need us.

252
00:24:02.323 --> 00:24:05.323
Let's go upstairs.
We'll party.

253
00:24:05.823 --> 00:24:06.823
Come on.

254
00:24:10.315 --> 00:24:11.315
Come. children.

255
00:24:18.325 --> 00:24:20.825
We should have fun today.

256
00:24:26.486 --> 00:24:31.486
Wherever the enemy goes.
all they find is destruction.

257
00:24:32.486 --> 00:24:34.986
That's the death sentence
for the German people.

258
00:24:36.486 --> 00:24:39.986
No power. no gas. no drinking
water. no coal. no traffic.

259
00:24:40.986 --> 00:24:47.486
If you destroy everything. our country
will go back to the Middle Ages.

260
00:24:47.986 --> 00:24:50.986
This order denies the people
any chance of survival.

261
00:24:51.986 --> 00:24:55.986
If the war is lost. what does it matter
that the people are lost too?

262
00:24:56.486 --> 00:25:01.986
The primary necessities of life of the
German people aren't relevant. right now.

263
00:25:02.486 --> 00:25:05.486
On the contrary.
We'd best destroy them ourselves.

264
00:25:05.986 --> 00:25:08.486
Our people turned out weak...

265
00:25:08.986 --> 00:25:12.486
...and according to the laws of nature.
they should die out.

266
00:25:12.986 --> 00:25:15.986
They're your people.
You're their Führer.

267
00:25:16.486 --> 00:25:18.986
What remains after this battle...

268
00:25:19.486 --> 00:25:23.986
...is only the inferior.
The superior will have fallen.

269
00:25:30.713 --> 00:25:34.213
Come along. You have to dance.

270
00:25:34.713 --> 00:25:37.713
Care to dance. Fräulein Braun?
-I'd love to.

271
00:26:02.361 --> 00:26:04.361
May I?
-Go ahead.

272
00:26:05.361 --> 00:26:06.361
What's wrong?

273
00:26:11.361 --> 00:26:14.361
We have to leave Berlin. Eva.
You must convince him.

274
00:26:18.361 --> 00:26:19.861
Or else. come with me.

275
00:26:28.939 --> 00:26:29.939
You'll die.

276
00:26:50.312 --> 00:26:53.312
Can somebody play some music?
I want to dance.

277
00:26:53.812 --> 00:26:54.812
Dance.

278
00:26:58.874 --> 00:27:00.874
Do you have a request?
-As long as it swings.

279
00:27:28.162 --> 00:27:29.662
Traudl.

280
00:27:35.302 --> 00:27:37.802
It's all so unreal.

281
00:27:38.302 --> 00:27:43.802
It's like a dream you
can't get out of.

282
00:27:44.302 --> 00:27:45.802
It keeps on going.

283
00:27:49.802 --> 00:27:52.302
Gerda. I don't feel well.

284
00:28:27.278 --> 00:28:28.778
Traudl. come.

285
00:28:48.048 --> 00:28:49.548
I did not move...

286
00:28:51.548 --> 00:28:54.048
I did not move
my command post.

287
00:28:55.396 --> 00:28:57.396
To the west? How so?

288
00:28:58.396 --> 00:29:00.896
I'm at 1000 meters from the enemy.
-General.

289
00:29:20.632 --> 00:29:22.632
And. general?

290
00:29:22.633 --> 00:29:25.632
I'll be executed.
-What? Why?

291
00:29:26.632 --> 00:29:30.632
They think I moved my
command post to the west.

292
00:29:31.632 --> 00:29:34.132
Be sensible. general.
-Come along.

293
00:29:51.067 --> 00:29:52.567
Schenck.
-Mohnke.

294
00:29:53.038 --> 00:29:57.538
I'm under the chancellery.
I'm commander of the citadel now.

295
00:29:58.038 --> 00:30:02.038
I need help.
-That will be difficult. Everything's gone.

296
00:30:02.538 --> 00:30:04.538
My assistant and I are
the only ones here.

297
00:30:05.411 --> 00:30:07.411
You're a doctor. aren't you?
-Yes. an internist.

298
00:30:07.911 --> 00:30:11.911
Commandeer a car and
bring all the medication...

299
00:30:12.411 --> 00:30:14.911
...you can find. to me.

300
00:30:15.411 --> 00:30:18.411
I'll do my best.
-Thanks. Hurry.

301
00:31:06.603 --> 00:31:08.603
I need to talk to the Führer.

302
00:31:09.603 --> 00:31:13.103
What about?
-I'm going to be executed.

303
00:31:16.603 --> 00:31:17.603
Wait here.

304
00:31:19.103 --> 00:31:20.103
Your weapon. please.

305
00:31:26.971 --> 00:31:28.103
Not here.

306
00:31:31.536 --> 00:31:35.036
Guard post 2.
Understood.

307
00:31:37.036 --> 00:31:38.536
General...

308
00:31:41.036 --> 00:31:42.536
Not you.

309
00:32:04.548 --> 00:32:07.548
What's going on here?
Why am I going to be executed?

310
00:32:08.048 --> 00:32:12.048
You know that any evasive manoeuvre
towards the west is forbidden.

311
00:32:12.548 --> 00:32:17.048
Officers who don't obey.
must be executed.

312
00:32:17.049 --> 00:32:20.548
What do you mean?
My troops have been fighting for days.

313
00:32:21.548 --> 00:32:25.548
My command post
is a kilometre away from the front line.

314
00:32:26.048 --> 00:32:27.548
Continue.

315
00:32:27.549 --> 00:32:32.048
Do you see this? I don't want you
to use that tone with me.

316
00:32:33.548 --> 00:32:36.548
And now. do whatever
you feel you must.

317
00:32:37.048 --> 00:32:41.048
It's best if you tell this to the
Führer yourself. Come along.

318
00:32:55.779 --> 00:32:59.779
You can't pass. Oberst.
-Orders from brigade führer Mohnke:

319
00:32:59.780 --> 00:33:02.779
I have to get into the hospital.
We need medication.

320
00:33:03.279 --> 00:33:05.779
There's nobody left.
They all took off.

321
00:33:06.279 --> 00:33:08.779
And the wounded?
-How should I know?

322
00:33:09.279 --> 00:33:11.279
I'm going to have a look.
You stay here.

323
00:33:11.466 --> 00:33:15.466
Be very careful.
There are lots of Russians here.

324
00:33:16.263 --> 00:33:20.763
See that? That's where the
Reich ends. Behind it. is Russkie land.

325
00:33:32.125 --> 00:33:33.625
May I?

326
00:33:33.626 --> 00:33:44.108
He's damned stubborn.
Why doesn't he let me do that?

327
00:34:42.891 --> 00:34:46.391
I should have been back by now.
Are you sure the Führer still needs me?

328
00:34:46.891 --> 00:34:49.891
Drink.
-Führer's orders.

329
00:34:50.391 --> 00:34:53.370
You made a big impression
on the Führer.

330
00:34:53.870 --> 00:34:55.870
But you don't think Steiner
will attack. do you?

331
00:34:56.370 --> 00:34:58.870
I doubt whether Steiner
is able to do anything...

332
00:34:59.370 --> 00:35:01.870
...but you probably know that
better than I do.

333
00:35:02.870 --> 00:35:05.870
If Steiner doesn't attack.
Berlin is lost.

334
00:35:15.156 --> 00:35:17.156
The Führer was impressed
with your report.

335
00:35:17.656 --> 00:35:21.656
He puts you in command of
the defence of Berlin.

336
00:35:22.656 --> 00:35:27.156
I'd have preferred it
if he executed me.

337
00:35:47.241 --> 00:35:49.241
Let them get closer.

338
00:35:50.599 --> 00:35:52.099
Tank alert.

339
00:35:52.100 --> 00:35:56.790
Take it easy. Wait. kid.
They're still too far.

340
00:36:45.059 --> 00:36:48.059
Is it German artillery that I hear?
-I'm afraid not.

341
00:36:48.559 --> 00:36:50.559
But hasn't Steiner's
attack started?

342
00:36:54.059 --> 00:36:56.559
You have to go as fast as you can.
Time is running out.

343
00:36:57.059 --> 00:36:59.059
But the Führer has
the situation under control.

344
00:37:00.059 --> 00:37:01.559
Steiner will make
all the difference.

345
00:37:02.559 --> 00:37:05.559
He says it will change
military history.

346
00:37:06.059 --> 00:37:09.559
Everybody. but the Führer. knows
that's a fantasy.

347
00:37:10.059 --> 00:37:15.059
I even wonder if he believes it himself.
-Why would he be playing games?

348
00:37:15.559 --> 00:37:17.059
What does he have to lose?

349
00:37:18.559 --> 00:37:19.559
I don't believe a word of it.

350
00:37:20.559 --> 00:37:23.058
The enemy made a breakthrough.

351
00:37:23.558 --> 00:37:27.058
They took Zossen and are advancing
towards Stahnsdorf.

352
00:37:27.558 --> 00:37:31.058
They're at the northern city border.
between Frohnau and Pankow.

353
00:37:31.558 --> 00:37:36.558
In the east. they reached
Lichtenberg. Mahlsdorf and Karlshorst.

354
00:37:37.058 --> 00:37:40.058
If Steiner attacks.
everything will be alright.

355
00:37:43.558 --> 00:37:45.058
Mein Führer...

356
00:37:46.558 --> 00:37:48.058
Steiner...

357
00:37:49.558 --> 00:37:52.058
Steiner didn't have enough force.

358
00:37:52.558 --> 00:37:55.058
The attack didn't take place.

359
00:38:10.691 --> 00:38:16.191
The following stay here:
Keitel. Jodl. Krebs and Burgdorf.

360
00:38:30.222 --> 00:38:35.222
That was an order.
Steiner's attack was an order.

361
00:38:35.722 --> 00:38:39.722
How dare you
ignore my orders?

362
00:38:41.722 --> 00:38:44.222
Is this what it came to?

363
00:38:45.722 --> 00:38:50.722
The military. everybody lied
to me. Even the SS.

364
00:38:51.222 --> 00:38:56.222
The generals are no more than
a bunch of disloyal cowards.

365
00:38:56.722 --> 00:38:58.722
I don't allow that...

366
00:38:59.222 --> 00:39:03.722
Cowards. traitors and incompetents.
-Führer. this is outrageous.

367
00:39:04.222 --> 00:39:07.722
The generals are the scum
of the German people.

368
00:39:08.222 --> 00:39:10.722
No sense of honour.

369
00:39:11.222 --> 00:39:15.222
You call yourself general because
you spent years at the academy...

370
00:39:16.222 --> 00:39:18.722
...where you only learnt
to use knife and fork.

371
00:39:19.222 --> 00:39:23.222
For years. the military
obstructed me.

372
00:39:23.722 --> 00:39:27.722
All you ever did is
thwart me.

373
00:39:28.456 --> 00:39:31.456
I should have had...

374
00:39:31.956 --> 00:39:36.456
...all the high officers executed.
Like Stalin did.

375
00:39:40.993 --> 00:39:43.493
I never went to the academy.

376
00:39:43.494 --> 00:39:49.993
But I conquered all
of Europe on my own.

377
00:39:54.592 --> 00:39:56.092
Traitors.

378
00:39:56.592 --> 00:40:01.092
I've been betrayed and deceived
from the start.

379
00:40:01.592 --> 00:40:06.091
Such enormous betrayal
of the German people.

380
00:40:07.091 --> 00:40:12.091
But all these traitors will pay.
With their own blood.

381
00:40:13.018 --> 00:40:15.018
They will drown
in their own blood.

382
00:40:17.518 --> 00:40:19.018
Relax. Gerda.

383
00:40:26.266 --> 00:40:29.766
All my orders have
been ignored.

384
00:40:31.266 --> 00:40:35.266
How can I be a leader
under these circumstances?

385
00:40:36.969 --> 00:40:38.969
It's over.

386
00:40:42.744 --> 00:40:45.744
The war is lost.

387
00:40:51.520 --> 00:40:55.020
But if you think this means
I'll leave Berlin...

388
00:40:55.520 --> 00:40:59.520
...you're wrong. I'd rather
shoot a bullet through my head.

389
00:41:04.166 --> 00:41:06.166
Do what you want.

390
00:41:26.152 --> 00:41:29.652
The Führer wasn't serious about
killing himself. was he?

391
00:41:30.152 --> 00:41:32.652
Frau Junge. Frau Christian.

392
00:41:36.152 --> 00:41:40.652
Get changed. In one hour.
a plane will take you south.

393
00:41:42.086 --> 00:41:44.086
Everything is lost.

394
00:41:44.586 --> 00:41:46.586
Completely lost.

395
00:41:50.086 --> 00:41:53.586
You know I'll stay with you.
You can't send me away.

396
00:42:05.402 --> 00:42:07.402
I'm staying too. mein Führer.

397
00:42:30.945 --> 00:42:31.945
Now what?

398
00:42:32.945 --> 00:42:34.445
Time to end this charade.

399
00:42:35.445 --> 00:42:39.445
Do you want us to stop fighting?
That's inconceivable.

400
00:42:39.945 --> 00:42:44.945
The Führer doesn't want us to capitulate.
No more November 1918. Ever.

401
00:42:45.445 --> 00:42:48.945
But he doesn't want to be in charge
anymore. He said: 'Do what you want'.

402
00:42:49.445 --> 00:42:52.444
Nobody can replace him.
He's the Führer.

403
00:42:52.944 --> 00:42:54.944
The Führer's confused.
He'll recover.

404
00:42:55.944 --> 00:42:58.444
Great.
And then what?

405
00:43:00.944 --> 00:43:03.944
No capitulation. That was
never his intention.

406
00:43:04.944 --> 00:43:07.444
We owe it to him.
-Hollow phrases.

407
00:43:07.944 --> 00:43:09.944
We have to act now.
Or it will be too late.

408
00:43:10.944 --> 00:43:13.444
You're only looking after yourself.
-Mind your words.

409
00:43:22.282 --> 00:43:23.782
Damn.

410
00:43:28.282 --> 00:43:32.282
We'll never get out of here alive.
It's all over.

411
00:43:32.782 --> 00:43:33.782
We've got to wait.

412
00:43:34.282 --> 00:43:37.782
Even the Führer doesn't believe in it
anymore. What will happen to us?

413
00:43:38.282 --> 00:43:42.282
Günsche says there's a tunnel
that goes under the Russian lines.

414
00:43:43.282 --> 00:43:45.782
Why did you say
you wanted to stay with him?

415
00:43:46.282 --> 00:43:49.782
I don't know.
Honestly.

416
00:43:52.282 --> 00:43:54.782
It stopped.
Let's go for a walk.

417
00:44:34.853 --> 00:44:36.353
Traudl.

418
00:44:36.853 --> 00:44:38.353
Look here.

419
00:44:59.840 --> 00:45:02.340
I'm lighting another one.

420
00:45:19.537 --> 00:45:22.037
Let's go down again.

421
00:45:50.819 --> 00:45:54.819
Where do they come from?
-Volkssturm. Drafted this afternoon.

422
00:45:55.319 --> 00:45:57.819
They have to get
out of the field of fire.

423
00:46:01.319 --> 00:46:05.319
The Volkssturm is under the
direct command of Dr. Goebbels.

424
00:46:08.357 --> 00:46:11.857
I want them to go away from there.
This is insane.

425
00:46:12.857 --> 00:46:14.357
I'll take the responsibility.

426
00:46:25.057 --> 00:46:28.557
I think this is wrong.
-Great.

427
00:46:30.057 --> 00:46:31.557
Stop. Lights out.

428
00:46:32.057 --> 00:46:34.557
Stop. Stay where you are.

429
00:46:35.057 --> 00:46:38.057
Stay where you are.
-Alright. Germans.

430
00:46:41.921 --> 00:46:45.921
Help. They want to kill us.
-What is all this?

431
00:46:45.922 --> 00:46:49.921
A Greifkommando.
-You're kidding.

432
00:46:59.413 --> 00:47:02.413
Stop it.
Let those men go.

433
00:47:02.913 --> 00:47:05.913
What's this?
You have no authority here.

434
00:47:06.413 --> 00:47:10.913
These men are on the run.
Traitors will be killed.

435
00:47:11.413 --> 00:47:14.913
They're old men. Civilians.
You can't do this.

436
00:47:19.564 --> 00:47:22.064
Who's going to stop me?
You maybe?

437
00:47:24.064 --> 00:47:26.064
Stop it. That's enough.

438
00:47:39.419 --> 00:47:40.919
Dismissed.

439
00:49:20.390 --> 00:49:22.390
This man's a doctor.

440
00:49:29.376 --> 00:49:31.876
Can you operate?
-Not really.

441
00:49:34.834 --> 00:49:38.834
Don't let the children
take too many toys.

442
00:49:39.334 --> 00:49:42.334
And not too much nightwear.
That's no longer needed.

443
00:49:42.834 --> 00:49:45.834
Herr Minister...
-Frau Junge. my family will arrive soon.

444
00:49:46.334 --> 00:49:50.334
Can you look after them for a moment?
Thank you.

445
00:49:50.834 --> 00:49:52.334
Brigade führer. what can I do for you?

446
00:49:52.834 --> 00:49:55.834
Your Volkssturm is an easy prey
for the Russians.

447
00:49:56.334 --> 00:49:58.834
They have neither combat experience
nor good weapons.

448
00:49:59.334 --> 00:50:04.334
Their unconditional belief
in the final victory makes up for that.

449
00:50:04.335 --> 00:50:08.834
Herr Minister. without weapons
these men can't fight.

450
00:50:09.334 --> 00:50:10.834
Their deaths will be pointless.

451
00:50:11.334 --> 00:50:13.834
I don't pity them.

452
00:50:15.334 --> 00:50:17.834
I repeat:
I don't pity them.

453
00:50:18.334 --> 00:50:20.834
The people called this
upon themselves.

454
00:50:21.834 --> 00:50:25.334
This may come as a surprise to you.
Don't fool yourself.

455
00:50:25.834 --> 00:50:29.334
We didn't force the people.
They gave us a mandate.

456
00:50:29.335 --> 00:50:32.834
And now they're paying for it.

457
00:50:49.193 --> 00:50:51.693
Eva. you have to leave the Führer.

458
00:50:52.193 --> 00:50:54.193
Don't be stupid.
This is about life and death.

459
00:50:54.693 --> 00:50:56.693
How can you say that?
Where are you?

460
00:50:57.693 --> 00:51:00.193
I decided
not to die in Berlin.

461
00:51:00.693 --> 00:51:05.192
Does my sister know where you are?
-Think about it. I'll call you back.

462
00:51:07.192 --> 00:51:09.692
Children. your room is to the right.

463
00:51:11.692 --> 00:51:13.192
Wait for me.

464
00:51:14.692 --> 00:51:18.192
Hello. Frau Goebbels.
-Good to see you. Frau Junge.

465
00:51:30.094 --> 00:51:32.094
Line up. children.

466
00:51:32.594 --> 00:51:34.594
Helga. come. Line up.

467
00:51:35.594 --> 00:51:40.094
Let's make ourselves look good and
then we go say hello to uncle Hitler.

468
00:51:44.094 --> 00:51:46.094
Do you remember the song?

469
00:52:24.114 --> 00:52:28.114
The best thing to do is to
shoot yourself in the mouth.

470
00:52:32.114 --> 00:52:35.114
You won't feel a thing.
You'll be dead right away.

471
00:52:36.114 --> 00:52:38.614
I want to be a beautiful corpse.
I'll take poison.

472
00:52:39.114 --> 00:52:42.114
If I have to die.
at least without any pain.

473
00:52:42.614 --> 00:52:44.114
That's definitely painless.

474
00:52:44.614 --> 00:52:49.114
It paralyses the nervous system
and the respiratory system.

475
00:52:49.614 --> 00:52:51.114
A matter of seconds.

476
00:52:53.114 --> 00:52:56.114
Can I have one too?
-Me too.

477
00:53:01.114 --> 00:53:05.614
Himmler provided me well.

478
00:53:22.729 --> 00:53:24.729
Thank you.

479
00:53:25.729 --> 00:53:30.229
I would have liked to give you
a nicer present.

480
00:53:37.802 --> 00:53:41.802
Berlin. 23 April 1945.

481
00:53:45.302 --> 00:53:50.301
Dear sister. I'm sorry
to write you this.

482
00:53:50.801 --> 00:53:55.301
But this is how it is. It could
be over any moment.

483
00:53:55.801 --> 00:53:58.801
First of all: Hermann isn't with us.

484
00:53:59.301 --> 00:54:02.801
But I'm sure
you'll see him again.

485
00:54:03.301 --> 00:54:08.301
He'll get through this
and he'll fight from Bavaria.

486
00:54:08.801 --> 00:54:12.301
The Führer lost all hope
of a good outcome.

487
00:54:13.801 --> 00:54:17.301
Dear son. I don't know
if you'll receive this letter.

488
00:54:18.301 --> 00:54:22.801
Maybe someone will allow me
to send you a last greeting.

489
00:54:23.301 --> 00:54:26.801
I stayed with daddy
against his will.

490
00:54:27.301 --> 00:54:30.301
Last Sunday. the Führer
wanted to help me escape.

491
00:54:30.801 --> 00:54:33.301
But you know your mother.
We have the same blood.

492
00:54:33.801 --> 00:54:37.301
I won't even think about it.
Our ideology's going down the drain...

493
00:54:37.801 --> 00:54:42.801
...and with it. everything that made life
beautiful and worthwhile.

494
00:54:43.301 --> 00:54:47.301
After the Führer and National Socialism.
there's nothing left to live for.

495
00:54:48.301 --> 00:54:50.801
That's why I brought
the children too.

496
00:54:51.301 --> 00:54:53.301
They're too good for the life
that awaits them.

497
00:54:53.801 --> 00:54:58.301
God will have mercy on me
if I bring them redemption myself.

498
00:55:05.806 --> 00:55:09.806
I'll wear my bracelet with the green
stone until the very end.

499
00:55:10.306 --> 00:55:15.306
After that. I want
you to always wear it.

500
00:55:16.806 --> 00:55:20.306
Unfortunately. my diamond watch
is with the watchmaker.

501
00:55:20.806 --> 00:55:24.806
I included the address below.
I hope you're lucky enough to get it.

502
00:55:25.806 --> 00:55:27.306
I want you to get it.

503
00:55:28.806 --> 00:55:32.306
You'll also get the bracelet
with the topaz pendant.

504
00:55:32.806 --> 00:55:35.306
A birthday present
from the Führer.

505
00:55:36.806 --> 00:55:40.306
I owe some money
to the Heise company.

506
00:55:41.306 --> 00:55:45.994
There may be more debts. but
no more than 1500 Reichsmarks.

507
00:55:47.494 --> 00:55:53.494
All correspondence with
the Führer must be burnt.

508
00:55:55.494 --> 00:56:01.494
I'm sending you some food and tobacco.
The coffee is also for Lindner and Kathl.

509
00:56:01.994 --> 00:56:07.494
The cigarettes are for Mandi. the tobacco
for daddy. the chocolate for mummy.

510
00:56:08.203 --> 00:56:12.703
I can't think of anything else.
That's it for today.

511
00:56:13.673 --> 00:56:17.173
Dear sister. I wish
you lots of happiness.

512
00:56:17.589 --> 00:56:21.089
And remember.
you will see Hermann again.

513
00:56:21.589 --> 00:56:25.089
The warmest regards
and a kiss from...

514
00:56:25.589 --> 00:56:27.089
...your sister.

515
00:57:16.640 --> 00:57:18.640
Inge.

516
00:58:06.173 --> 00:58:11.173
Listen. Keitel.
I want you to leave this evening.

517
00:58:11.673 --> 00:58:15.173
Go to Dönitz and help him
with the organisation.

518
00:58:15.673 --> 00:58:18.673
Things have to be
started up again.

519
00:58:20.173 --> 00:58:22.173
I don't understand you.

520
00:58:22.673 --> 00:58:26.173
We have no more oil fields.
That's catastrophic.

521
00:58:26.652 --> 00:58:32.152
It makes any serious operation
impossible.

522
00:58:32.173 --> 00:58:38.673
When everything has been solved
here. we must get the oil fields back.

523
00:58:43.173 --> 00:58:46.173
Any questions?
-No. mein Führer.

524
00:58:46.673 --> 00:58:49.173
Good.
Have a good trip.

525
01:00:18.515 --> 01:00:22.015
...do you agree that I take charge...

526
01:00:22.515 --> 01:00:25.515
...with complete freedom of action?

527
01:00:26.015 --> 01:00:28.015
If I receive no reply
by 2200 hours...

528
01:00:28.515 --> 01:00:31.421
...I'll assume you have
been incapacitated.

529
01:00:31.921 --> 01:00:35.421
I will then act on behalf
of the country and the motherland.

530
01:00:36.421 --> 01:00:38.921
That's high treason.
And betrayal of you.

531
01:00:39.421 --> 01:00:41.921
Göring's concerns are not
entirely unjustified.

532
01:00:42.421 --> 01:00:45.421
If our communication
system fails...

533
01:00:45.921 --> 01:00:48.921
...we'll be cut off
from the outside world.

534
01:00:49.421 --> 01:00:51.421
We won't be able
to issue orders anymore.

535
01:00:51.921 --> 01:00:54.421
I think Göring wants to
seize the power.

536
01:00:55.421 --> 01:00:57.921
I never trusted his clique
on the Obersalzberg.

537
01:00:58.921 --> 01:01:00.421
This looks like a coup.

538
01:01:00.921 --> 01:01:04.421
The loser. the sponger.

539
01:01:04.921 --> 01:01:07.421
A parvenu. a lazy bastard.

540
01:01:08.515 --> 01:01:13.015
How dare he say
I'm incapacitated?

541
01:01:14.015 --> 01:01:17.015
Hello.
-How did you get into Berlin?

542
01:01:17.515 --> 01:01:20.015
It wasn't easy.
but I must speak to the Führer.

543
01:01:21.015 --> 01:01:23.015
If I were you.
I'd wait a bit.

544
01:01:23.515 --> 01:01:26.515
The Luftwaffe.
What did he turn that into?

545
01:01:27.015 --> 01:01:30.015
For that alone.
he should be executed.

546
01:01:30.515 --> 01:01:36.015
This morphine addict
corrupted the country.

547
01:01:37.015 --> 01:01:38.515
And now this.

548
01:01:39.515 --> 01:01:42.015
He's betraying me.

549
01:01:43.515 --> 01:01:46.515
Me of all people.

550
01:01:46.516 --> 01:01:56.515
I want Göring stripped
of his power. right away.

551
01:01:57.515 --> 01:02:00.015
And. in case I don't
survive the war...

552
01:02:00.515 --> 01:02:03.514
...he must be
executed immediately.

553
01:02:06.014 --> 01:02:10.014
What's going to happen to us?
Is there any hope left?

554
01:02:12.514 --> 01:02:15.514
Frau Junge. leave from
here before it's too late.

555
01:02:16.014 --> 01:02:20.014
The Führer wants to stay.
We can't leave him behind. can we?

556
01:02:20.015 --> 01:02:25.514
He doesn't need anybody for what
awaits him. And least of all you.

557
01:02:26.514 --> 01:02:30.514
But Herr Goebbels and his wife
stay here. And the children.

558
01:02:39.514 --> 01:02:41.514
But the children...

559
01:02:45.014 --> 01:02:47.014
I have always believed...

560
01:02:48.514 --> 01:02:51.514
...that there was a way out.

561
01:02:58.014 --> 01:03:00.014
Come in.

562
01:03:02.014 --> 01:03:04.014
Albert. Hello.

563
01:03:15.014 --> 01:03:17.014
You have a fever.

564
01:03:17.514 --> 01:03:20.514
Albert. I can't stand
it anymore.

565
01:03:22.514 --> 01:03:25.014
Why don't you leave with
the children. Magda?

566
01:03:25.514 --> 01:03:28.014
Leave?
And go where?

567
01:03:28.514 --> 01:03:33.014
I can arrange for you to be
taken to Schwanenwerder by barge.

568
01:03:33.514 --> 01:03:37.014
You can hide
until everything's over.

569
01:03:37.514 --> 01:03:39.514
It won't be long now anyway.

570
01:03:40.014 --> 01:03:42.014
I thought about it.

571
01:03:43.514 --> 01:03:48.514
My children cannot grow up
in a world without National Socialism.

572
01:03:51.514 --> 01:03:56.014
Think about it. The children
have a right to a future.

573
01:04:00.014 --> 01:04:04.514
If National Socialism dies.
there will be no future.

574
01:04:20.285 --> 01:04:22.785
I can't believe
you really want that.

575
01:04:24.785 --> 01:04:27.285
Go now.

576
01:04:56.920 --> 01:04:58.920
Come in.

577
01:05:02.920 --> 01:05:04.920
I knew you'd come.

578
01:05:05.420 --> 01:05:08.420
You wouldn't desert
the Führer.

579
01:05:12.291 --> 01:05:17.791
I've come to say goodbye to the Führer.
I'm going back to Hamburg tonight.

580
01:05:18.291 --> 01:05:20.791
Of course. you must go.
Sit down.

581
01:05:23.291 --> 01:05:26.291
I took some furniture
you designed.

582
01:05:26.291 --> 01:05:28.742
I couldn't leave it behind.

583
01:05:29.242 --> 01:05:33.242
Please. you must
not have eaten all day.

584
01:05:34.242 --> 01:05:35.742
That's true.

585
01:05:40.242 --> 01:05:45.242
It's very important that you came.
It shows him you're on his side.

586
01:05:45.742 --> 01:05:47.742
Did he ever doubt that?

587
01:05:49.242 --> 01:05:52.742
Lately. he often thought
you were against him too.

588
01:05:53.242 --> 01:05:56.742
I always said you'd come
and here you are.

589
01:06:01.242 --> 01:06:04.742
I think he liked it that you
advised him to stay in Berlin.

590
01:06:05.242 --> 01:06:07.242
I also think it's best.

591
01:06:10.242 --> 01:06:12.242
And. you know...

592
01:06:13.242 --> 01:06:15.242
...it may sound strange...

593
01:06:17.242 --> 01:06:22.242
...but I'm really happy here.
And I'm not afraid.

594
01:06:47.936 --> 01:06:52.436
You came.
-Mein Führer. I...

595
01:06:52.437 --> 01:06:54.436
It's good.

596
01:06:55.936 --> 01:06:57.436
Let's sit down.

597
01:07:14.638 --> 01:07:19.638
I had great plans
for the Germans and the world.

598
01:07:21.138 --> 01:07:26.138
Nobody understood me.
Not even my old brothers in arms.

599
01:07:30.138 --> 01:07:36.137
The opportunities we had.
The whole world was ours to grab.

600
01:07:39.006 --> 01:07:40.506
Too late.

601
01:07:46.506 --> 01:07:51.506
I can only be proud for openly
fighting the Jews...

602
01:07:53.006 --> 01:07:57.006
...and for cleansing the Lebensraum
from the Jewish poison.

603
01:08:01.506 --> 01:08:05.506
I don't find it hard to continue.
One brief moment...

604
01:08:05.507 --> 01:08:15.506
...and then eternal peace.

605
01:08:19.506 --> 01:08:22.506
But please spare the people.
mein Führer.

606
01:08:22.507 --> 01:08:28.006
If my people cannot endure
this ordeal...

607
01:08:28.007 --> 01:08:31.006
...I won't shed a tear.

608
01:08:31.506 --> 01:08:33.506
They get what they deserve.

609
01:08:34.006 --> 01:08:39.506
They called this fate
upon themselves.

610
01:08:44.506 --> 01:08:46.506
For months...

611
01:08:48.006 --> 01:08:50.006
...I have to tell you this...

612
01:08:51.506 --> 01:08:55.006
...for months I have sabotaged
your orders for destruction.

613
01:08:57.006 --> 01:09:03.506
I not only ignored your orders.
but even acted against them.

614
01:09:08.504 --> 01:09:10.004
I had to tell you.

615
01:09:18.918 --> 01:09:22.918
This never compromised
my personal loyalty to you.

616
01:09:35.633 --> 01:09:38.133
So you're leaving.

617
01:09:39.328 --> 01:09:40.828
Good.

618
01:09:41.328 --> 01:09:42.828
Goodbye.

619
01:09:53.960 --> 01:09:55.960
I wish you all the best.

620
01:10:17.063 --> 01:10:20.563
Eat well. gentlemen.

621
01:11:14.027 --> 01:11:15.527
Peter.

622
01:11:24.221 --> 01:11:26.721
It's alright. son.

623
01:11:42.853 --> 01:11:44.353
He has a fever.

624
01:11:46.420 --> 01:11:47.420
Yes. but he's alive.

625
01:12:11.270 --> 01:12:15.270
Loyalty and courage
still exist in this world.

626
01:12:15.770 --> 01:12:18.770
Ritter von Greim
and Fräulein Reitsch. how good...

627
01:12:21.770 --> 01:12:25.770
...that the both of you arrived
more or less unharmed.

628
01:12:26.770 --> 01:12:27.770
Sit down.

629
01:12:29.270 --> 01:12:32.270
We came under heavy fire. but
still arrived in Gatow.

630
01:12:32.770 --> 01:12:35.270
From there.
we couldn't continue.

631
01:12:36.270 --> 01:12:40.270
We flew in a Fieseler Storch.
over the Russian lines...

632
01:12:41.270 --> 01:12:43.770
...and landed on the
East-West axis. close to here.

633
01:12:44.270 --> 01:12:46.770
Before landing. the Soviets
had a go at us.

634
01:12:48.365 --> 01:12:52.865
General Von Greim. I appoint you
supreme commander of the Luftwaffe.

635
01:12:53.865 --> 01:12:56.365
I hereby promote you
to General-Feldmarschall.

636
01:12:57.423 --> 01:12:59.923
A big responsibility
rests on your shoulders.

637
01:13:00.422 --> 01:13:03.422
You have to rebuild the
Luftwaffe from scratch.

638
01:13:03.922 --> 01:13:06.422
Many mistakes have been made.
Be ruthless.

639
01:13:07.922 --> 01:13:10.922
Life doesn't forgive weakness.

640
01:13:12.922 --> 01:13:18.422
This so-called humanity
is religious drivel.

641
01:13:19.922 --> 01:13:24.922
Compassion is an eternal sin.
To feel compassion for the weak...

642
01:13:25.422 --> 01:13:26.922
...is a betrayal of nature.

643
01:13:27.922 --> 01:13:32.922
The strong can only triumph
if the weak are exterminated.

644
01:13:33.422 --> 01:13:37.035
Being loyal to this law.
I've never had compassion.

645
01:13:37.035 --> 01:13:42.960
Being loyal to this law.
I've never had compassion.

646
01:13:44.495 --> 01:13:48.495
I've always been ruthless
when faced with internal...

647
01:13:48.995 --> 01:13:52.995
...opposition from other races.
And that's the only way.

648
01:13:54.995 --> 01:13:56.995
Apes. for instance....

649
01:13:57.950 --> 01:14:02.450
...kill all the odd ones.

650
01:14:02.950 --> 01:14:08.450
And what applies to apes.
must definitely apply to humans.

651
01:14:14.465 --> 01:14:16.465
Himmler made an offer to surrender...

652
01:14:16.466 --> 01:14:21.965
...to the allied powers.

653
01:14:22.465 --> 01:14:23.965
Via Count Bernadotte.

654
01:14:22.265 --> 01:14:24.765
A message from English radio.

655
01:14:29.265 --> 01:14:34.265
Himmler.
Himmler of all people.

656
01:14:35.590 --> 01:14:42.590
The most loyal of my loyals.
That's the worst betrayal.

657
01:14:46.090 --> 01:14:49.590
Göring. he was corrupt.
Always has been.

658
01:14:50.090 --> 01:14:56.090
Speer. an absent-minded artist.
All the others: yes.

659
01:14:56.590 --> 01:15:02.590
But Himmler?
Has he gone insane?

660
01:15:03.090 --> 01:15:07.090
He must have told
them I'm sick.

661
01:15:07.590 --> 01:15:09.590
Maybe even dead.

662
01:15:15.590 --> 01:15:20.090
Leave me alone with Ritter Von Greim
and Fräulein Reitsch.

663
01:15:21.590 --> 01:15:26.090
And get Fegelein.
-We don't know where he is.

664
01:15:26.590 --> 01:15:30.090
What? He's Himmler's assistant.
He must be available.

665
01:15:30.091 --> 01:15:34.590
We haven't seen him for days.
-I want a report immediately.

666
01:15:37.590 --> 01:15:39.090
Please stay here. Doctor.

667
01:15:44.090 --> 01:15:48.090
You and Greim must go as quickly
as possible. Fly to Dönitz.

668
01:15:48.091 --> 01:15:54.090
Tell him to do anything
it takes to punish Himmler.

669
01:15:54.590 --> 01:15:58.590
We've decided to
die with you.

670
01:16:01.090 --> 01:16:03.590
Thank you for this proof of loyalty.

671
01:16:05.090 --> 01:16:08.590
But Himmler must die.
He committed treason.

672
01:16:08.591 --> 01:16:13.091
He's no longer privvy
to my plans.

673
01:16:13.591 --> 01:16:14.591
Mein Führer?

674
01:16:15.091 --> 01:16:18.591
Do you think I'll sit and wait until
those Jewish swine slaughter me?

675
01:16:19.091 --> 01:16:23.091
This is part of a huge decoy manoeuvre.
I've allowed the enemy...

676
01:16:23.092 --> 01:16:28.091
...to invade the Reich and they
think they've won.

677
01:16:28.591 --> 01:16:32.091
But mark my words: they have
another thing coming.

678
01:16:32.092 --> 01:16:36.091
Dönitz is mobilising in the north.
Kesselring in the south.

679
01:16:36.591 --> 01:16:40.591
We'll surround the enemy
and crush them.

680
01:16:41.091 --> 01:16:46.091
From Prague. three armies will attack
the Russians. simultaneously. from the back.

681
01:16:46.591 --> 01:16:51.591
I didn't know we still had
so many reserve troops.

682
01:16:52.591 --> 01:16:56.091
I made sure you'll soon have
a 1000 of the most modern...

683
01:16:56.092 --> 01:17:00.091
...jets at your disposal.

684
01:17:00.591 --> 01:17:04.591
With those. you can make the
Luftwaffe ready for battle again.

685
01:17:05.091 --> 01:17:09.591
I kneel to your genius. at the
altar of the motherland.

686
01:17:23.890 --> 01:17:25.390
Heil. mein Führer.

687
01:17:28.390 --> 01:17:31.390
You also request to leave Berlin?

688
01:17:32.890 --> 01:17:36.890
Mein Führer. as you know.
all medical departments...

689
01:17:37.390 --> 01:17:40.390
...that fall under the SS and Himmler.
have left Berlin.

690
01:17:41.390 --> 01:17:45.390
Himmler is a traitor.
He won't escape punishment.

691
01:17:45.890 --> 01:17:50.537
Mein Führer. as Reichsarzt SS.
I have no more work here.

692
01:17:51.537 --> 01:17:55.038
Your request to leave Berlin
is unacceptable.

693
01:17:56.538 --> 01:17:58.538
My family...

694
01:18:00.038 --> 01:18:03.038
If the Russians...
I must leave.

695
01:18:03.538 --> 01:18:05.038
You did nothing wrong.

696
01:18:06.038 --> 01:18:11.038
Future generations will thank you
for you medical research.

697
01:18:11.538 --> 01:18:13.538
I take all the responsibility.

698
01:18:19.538 --> 01:18:22.038
We'll talk about it later.

699
01:18:35.811 --> 01:18:39.811
Gruppenführer Fegelein cannot
be found. He's not in the bunker.

700
01:18:40.311 --> 01:18:42.811
What. you can't find Fegelein?

701
01:18:43.811 --> 01:18:47.811
Keep searching.
I need to talk to him. Immediately.

702
01:18:48.811 --> 01:18:52.811
If he left just like that.
that's desertion. Treason.

703
01:18:53.311 --> 01:18:54.811
Bring me Fegelein.

704
01:18:55.311 --> 01:18:57.811
Fegelein. Fegelein.

705
01:19:08.850 --> 01:19:11.850
Daddy. why are you wearing
your Sunday uniform?

706
01:19:14.850 --> 01:19:19.350
Ernst. is something wrong?
-No.

707
01:19:19.850 --> 01:19:21.350
Thank you.

708
01:19:21.850 --> 01:19:23.350
Brigitte is hungry too.

709
01:19:25.350 --> 01:19:28.850
Ilse. you should
eat something as well.

710
01:19:30.850 --> 01:19:32.850
Thank you.
-There you go.

711
01:19:37.350 --> 01:19:38.850
Thank you.

712
01:20:30.731 --> 01:20:34.231
What is it?
-Gruppenführer. you're under arrest.

713
01:20:35.231 --> 01:20:36.731
What?
-You're suspected of desertion.

714
01:20:37.231 --> 01:20:39.231
Get dressed.
You'll come with us.

715
01:20:44.231 --> 01:20:45.731
Search the room.

716
01:20:46.231 --> 01:20:49.231
Let go of me.
You can't give me orders.

717
01:20:51.231 --> 01:20:54.231
You can't have Hermann
executed. can you?

718
01:20:54.731 --> 01:20:57.731
There's no doubt.
He wanted to flee.

719
01:20:57.732 --> 01:21:01.231
What does it matter?
Everything's over.

720
01:21:02.231 --> 01:21:04.731
Think of my poor sister.
She's pregnant by Hermann.

721
01:21:04.732 --> 01:21:08.231
He collaborated with Himmler.
He's a traitor.

722
01:21:11.231 --> 01:21:16.231
There's no mercy for traitors.
No compassion for them.

723
01:21:18.231 --> 01:21:21.231
He'll be court-martialled
and executed.

724
01:21:22.231 --> 01:21:24.231
What's the point of that?

725
01:21:26.231 --> 01:21:27.731
It is my wish.

726
01:21:41.072 --> 01:21:42.072
You're the Führer.

727
01:21:45.764 --> 01:21:46.764
Speak.

728
01:21:47.264 --> 01:21:49.764
The Russians are advancing
more and more.

729
01:21:50.264 --> 01:21:53.264
There are no more reserves.
Supplies from the air are impossible.

730
01:21:53.764 --> 01:21:56.264
There is no ammunition coming
in anymore.

731
01:22:00.264 --> 01:22:02.764
In the north. the Russians are standing
in front of the Weidendammer bridge.

732
01:22:03.264 --> 01:22:06.264
In the east: Lustgarten.
South: Potsdammer Platz.

733
01:22:06.764 --> 01:22:10.264
West: Tiergarten. about 400 metres
away from the chancellery.

734
01:22:11.264 --> 01:22:14.264
How long can you hold out?
-At most. two days.

735
01:22:15.264 --> 01:22:17.764
Including the government area?
-Yes.

736
01:22:18.764 --> 01:22:23.764
As a soldier. I suggest we
flee Berlin. It's surrounded.

737
01:22:24.264 --> 01:22:30.264
The battle of Berlin killed about
20.000 of our best officers.

738
01:22:30.265 --> 01:22:33.764
That's what young people are for.

739
01:22:34.764 --> 01:22:37.764
What you suggest is insane.
Ridiculous.

740
01:22:38.264 --> 01:22:41.264
Think of the thousands of wounded.
We can't help them.

741
01:22:41.265 --> 01:22:45.764
Mein Führer. the orders have been written.
I give you my word...

742
01:22:46.264 --> 01:22:50.764
The Führer cannot make a honourless
disappearance from world history.

743
01:22:51.264 --> 01:22:55.264
Even if an advance is successful...

744
01:22:55.764 --> 01:22:58.764
...I'll end up in another
troublesome situation.

745
01:22:59.264 --> 01:23:04.264
I'd have to stay in the open air
or on a farm...

746
01:23:04.764 --> 01:23:06.264
...and wait for the end.

747
01:23:07.764 --> 01:23:13.264
Wenck is advancing with the 12th army.
He can join the 9th...

748
01:23:13.592 --> 01:23:17.592
...and give the Russians
the final blow.

749
01:23:18.264 --> 01:23:22.264
Wenck's an excellent fellow.
Send a telegram to Keitel:

750
01:23:25.264 --> 01:23:30.764
Immediately report to me the following:
1. Where are Wenck's vanguard located?

751
01:23:31.764 --> 01:23:34.264
2. When will they attack again?

752
01:23:35.264 --> 01:23:40.764
3. Where is the 9th army?
4. Where will the 9th make a breakthrough?

753
01:23:42.764 --> 01:23:47.264
You'll see. gentlemen.
I'll be right.

754
01:23:47.764 --> 01:23:50.264
Wenck will come.

755
01:23:56.479 --> 01:23:58.479
Wenck will come.

756
01:24:11.171 --> 01:24:15.171
I want to know if Wenck
can do anything at all.

757
01:24:15.671 --> 01:24:20.171
It's unlikely that Wenck's
small amount of troops...

758
01:24:20.671 --> 01:24:25.171
What's unlikely about the offensive?
-Wenck can't do anything anymore.

759
01:24:25.671 --> 01:24:29.671
Then why don't you tell the Führer that?
Has everybody gone mad?

760
01:24:30.171 --> 01:24:33.171
Do you think the Führer doesn't know?
He'll never surrender.

761
01:24:33.671 --> 01:24:37.171
And neither will we. I've been
through that once. Never again.

762
01:24:37.671 --> 01:24:39.671
Come along. I have to go.

763
01:24:49.399 --> 01:24:50.899
Stop right there.

764
01:25:02.467 --> 01:25:03.967
Heil Hitler.

765
01:25:50.699 --> 01:25:53.199
Excuse me. I fell asleep.

766
01:25:53.699 --> 01:25:55.699
Did you get some rest. my child?

767
01:25:59.041 --> 01:26:01.041
In shorthand.

768
01:26:07.041 --> 01:26:10.541
My political will.

769
01:26:11.549 --> 01:26:16.549
More than 30 years have passed...

770
01:26:16.550 --> 01:26:21.049
...since I made my contribution
as a volunteer...

771
01:26:21.050 --> 01:26:25.049
...during the first World War.

772
01:26:25.549 --> 01:26:30.549
During those 30 years.
I learnt to think. act and live...

773
01:26:31.049 --> 01:26:34.049
...out of love and loyalty
for my people.

774
01:26:37.832 --> 01:26:41.332
Excuse me. The shooting.
-Please sit down.

775
01:26:44.910 --> 01:26:47.410
Centuries will pass...

776
01:26:47.910 --> 01:26:51.910
...but from the ruins
of our cities and monuments...

777
01:26:51.911 --> 01:26:57.410
...the hatred
of the people...

778
01:26:57.411 --> 01:27:00.410
...who did this to us.
will continue to flare up.

779
01:27:00.910 --> 01:27:04.910
International Judaism and
its allies.

780
01:27:15.653 --> 01:27:17.653
What is it. Herr Minister?

781
01:27:21.153 --> 01:27:23.653
Imagine this.
The Führer wants me to leave Berlin.

782
01:27:24.653 --> 01:27:26.653
He ordered it.

783
01:27:28.653 --> 01:27:32.153
I've never ignored an order
from the Führer.

784
01:27:40.496 --> 01:27:45.996
But I will ignore this order.
I'll stay with the Führer.

785
01:27:49.563 --> 01:27:51.563
Please. Frau Junge...

786
01:27:53.563 --> 01:27:56.563
...I want to dictate my will to you.

787
01:27:58.563 --> 01:28:01.563
I'm typing
the Führer's will.

788
01:28:02.563 --> 01:28:04.563
Good.

789
01:28:05.563 --> 01:28:08.063
I understand.
Some other time.

790
01:28:14.979 --> 01:28:19.979
Mein Führer. according to the racial law
I'm obliged to ask you:

791
01:28:20.479 --> 01:28:22.979
Mein Führer. are you
of Aryan descent?

792
01:28:27.719 --> 01:28:30.219
Can I see your identity card?

793
01:28:31.262 --> 01:28:34.262
You're talking to the Führer here.
-Alright then.

794
01:28:34.762 --> 01:28:38.262
And you. Fräulein Braun.
are you of Aryan descent?

795
01:28:39.062 --> 01:28:42.062
Then there's nothing
to stop us.

796
01:28:42.562 --> 01:28:46.062
I'm asking you now:
Do you. mein Führer. Adolf Hitler...

797
01:28:46.562 --> 01:28:51.562
...take Eva Braun. present here.
as your wife? Answer 'yes'.

798
01:28:53.562 --> 01:28:57.062
Do you. Eva Braun. take Führer
Adolf Hitler. present here...

799
01:28:57.562 --> 01:29:00.562
...as your husband?
Answer 'yes'.

800
01:29:02.062 --> 01:29:05.062
Then I declare you
man and wife.

801
01:29:42.813 --> 01:29:44.813
Two men here.

802
01:29:46.997 --> 01:29:48.497
Everything will be alright.

803
01:29:50.336 --> 01:29:52.836
You must go to the Führer right away.
-Now?

804
01:30:11.729 --> 01:30:15.729
How long can we hold out?
-Twenty hours. no more.

805
01:30:17.229 --> 01:30:22.729
The Russians are close. At the moment.
we forced them to stop.

806
01:30:23.229 --> 01:30:28.229
You know. Mohnke. The western
democracies are decadent.

807
01:30:28.729 --> 01:30:33.729
They'll succumb to
the people from the east.

808
01:30:36.729 --> 01:30:39.229
All the best. Thank you.

809
01:30:40.229 --> 01:30:43.229
It wasn't just for Germany.

810
01:31:02.343 --> 01:31:04.343
A message from Keitel.

811
01:31:07.343 --> 01:31:10.525
1. Wenck's vanguard are
stuck south of Schwielowsee.

812
01:31:11.025 --> 01:31:14.525
2. The 12th army can't continue
the attack on Berlin.

813
01:31:15.525 --> 01:31:19.025
3. The 9th army is
completely surrounded.

814
01:31:38.180 --> 01:31:43.180
What do we do when the last
ammunition reserves have been exhausted?

815
01:31:44.180 --> 01:31:47.180
I'll never surrender. Never.

816
01:31:49.180 --> 01:31:54.180
I forbid you. and the other
commanders. to surrender.

817
01:32:05.702 --> 01:32:11.202
Listen. Günsche. My wife and I
are going to commit suicide.

818
01:32:11.702 --> 01:32:15.702
I don't want my corpse
exposed by the Russians.

819
01:32:16.202 --> 01:32:19.202
I don't want them to get me.
dead or alive.

820
01:32:19.702 --> 01:32:23.202
I want to be burnt
and never to be found.

821
01:32:27.202 --> 01:32:30.202
Günsche. I want you to promise me...

822
01:32:30.702 --> 01:32:35.702
...that you will do
all that it takes.

823
01:32:36.202 --> 01:32:38.202
Mein Führer...

824
01:32:38.203 --> 01:32:42.202
...this is a terrible order.
but I will execute it.

825
01:33:08.363 --> 01:33:11.363
Kempka.
-Erich. I need 200 litres of petrol.

826
01:33:11.364 --> 01:33:14.863
Are you mad?
Where should I find them?

827
01:33:15.363 --> 01:33:17.363
From the parked vehicles.

828
01:33:18.363 --> 01:33:20.863
What's all that petrol for?
-I can't say.

829
01:33:36.868 --> 01:33:39.868
Come. please.
The Führer wants to see us.

830
01:33:48.937 --> 01:33:51.437
Should I tell the Führer
you're indisposed?

831
01:33:52.437 --> 01:33:55.437
It's only my collapsed lung.

832
01:33:57.396 --> 01:33:59.396
I'll die soon anyway.

833
01:34:43.046 --> 01:34:45.046
Excuse me.

834
01:34:57.103 --> 01:34:59.103
Over here. Herr Professor.

835
01:35:07.739 --> 01:35:10.239
One moment. please.

836
01:35:19.099 --> 01:35:20.599
Excuse me.

837
01:35:52.664 --> 01:35:56.664
I'm sorry to interrupt
your important work.

838
01:35:57.164 --> 01:36:01.164
Mein Führer. keep faith
in the final victory.

839
01:36:01.664 --> 01:36:06.164
Lead us
and we shall follow.

840
01:36:09.805 --> 01:36:11.305
Come along.

841
01:36:18.277 --> 01:36:20.277
Join the gang.

842
01:36:22.422 --> 01:36:24.922
Come. Have a drink.

843
01:36:25.922 --> 01:36:29.422
Besides drinking. there's little we can do.
-Do sit down.

844
01:36:29.922 --> 01:36:36.422
That's better.
Yes. the situation is pretty shitty.

845
01:36:40.422 --> 01:36:43.922
Can we sit down?
-Please do. Fräulein...

846
01:36:44.422 --> 01:36:48.422
Frau...
-That's Frau Hitler.

847
01:36:50.922 --> 01:36:52.422
It's alright.

848
01:36:54.422 --> 01:36:56.922
A pity we can't go
outside anymore.

849
01:36:57.422 --> 01:37:00.422
Only if you want
to die a heroic death.

850
01:37:00.922 --> 01:37:06.422
Fritz. control yourself a bit.
-Yes. Control.

851
01:37:07.422 --> 01:37:08.922
Take cover.

852
01:37:29.519 --> 01:37:33.019
What are you doing here?
-I have to report to the Führer.

853
01:37:33.519 --> 01:37:35.519
You can't right now.
Sit down.

854
01:37:36.019 --> 01:37:38.019
Sit. Drink.

855
01:37:42.019 --> 01:37:44.019
Let me introduce Frau Hitler.

856
01:37:44.020 --> 01:37:48.019
So young and so many decorations.
You must be proud.

857
01:37:51.019 --> 01:37:53.519
Excuse me.
I'm not used to drinking anymore.

858
01:37:54.519 --> 01:37:57.019
You can use our toilet.

859
01:38:04.497 --> 01:38:09.497
If your hand shakes. the bullet
might only hit an optic nerve.

860
01:38:09.997 --> 01:38:14.497
That's why it's good
to also take the poison.

861
01:38:14.997 --> 01:38:19.497
When you bite through the capsule.
pull the trigger.

862
01:38:19.997 --> 01:38:21.997
Will I have enough time?

863
01:38:22.997 --> 01:38:25.497
The poison starts working
after one or two seconds.

864
01:38:42.200 --> 01:38:44.700
Tornow. you too.

865
01:38:53.370 --> 01:38:54.870
Come Blondi.

866
01:39:25.247 --> 01:39:27.747
You know. Frau Junge.
I've known...

867
01:39:28.747 --> 01:39:31.247
my husband for
more than 15 years.

868
01:39:31.747 --> 01:39:36.247
But when I think about it.
I know nothing about him.

869
01:39:36.747 --> 01:39:38.747
Even though he likes to talk.

870
01:39:41.747 --> 01:39:46.247
I longed for Berlin.
but he's so different now.

871
01:39:46.747 --> 01:39:50.247
He only talks about dogs
and vegetarian food now.

872
01:39:50.747 --> 01:39:53.247
I hate Blondi.

873
01:39:54.747 --> 01:39:59.747
I sometimes kick her and Adolf
then wonders why she acts strange.

874
01:40:10.247 --> 01:40:12.747
I think he doesn't want anybody
to really know him.

875
01:40:15.747 --> 01:40:20.247
...he can be so caring
in his private life.

876
01:40:21.747 --> 01:40:26.247
And then he uses
that rude language again.

877
01:40:27.247 --> 01:40:29.247
When he's the Führer. you mean?

878
01:40:30.747 --> 01:40:33.747
Come. let's smoke another one.

879
01:40:54.650 --> 01:40:56.150
I'm sorry.

880
01:40:58.137 --> 01:41:02.137
You have so many worries
and here I am. whining.

881
01:41:03.137 --> 01:41:06.637
Frau Junge. I'm giving you this coat
as a goodbye present.

882
01:41:07.637 --> 01:41:12.137
I like fashionable ladies.
I want you to enjoy it.

883
01:41:13.137 --> 01:41:15.637
What a surprise. Thank you.

884
01:41:17.137 --> 01:41:20.637
I just don't know where and when
I can wear it.

885
01:41:22.137 --> 01:41:25.137
Please. try to get out of here.

886
01:41:26.637 --> 01:41:28.137
Promise me.

887
01:42:53.911 --> 01:42:58.518
Thank you. That was very good.
Fräulein Manziarly.

888
01:43:18.662 --> 01:43:22.662
The time has come. It's finished.

889
01:43:59.896 --> 01:44:01.896
The Führer wants to say goodbye.
Come with me.

890
01:44:32.569 --> 01:44:35.569
You're the bravest mother
of the Reich.

891
01:44:36.069 --> 01:44:40.069
Führer. you made me the happiest
woman in Germany.

892
01:45:03.208 --> 01:45:05.208
Salute my beautiful Bavaria.

893
01:45:27.845 --> 01:45:29.845
Children. what are you doing here?

894
01:45:30.345 --> 01:45:32.845
We want to see aunt Eva
and uncle Hitler.

895
01:45:33.345 --> 01:45:36.845
Have you eaten anything yet?
-Only breakfast.

896
01:45:38.345 --> 01:45:41.845
Stay here. I'll get something to eat.
I'll be right back.

897
01:45:50.655 --> 01:45:55.155
Comrades. this is the
latest news from the outside.

898
01:45:55.655 --> 01:46:00.655
Berlin is full of warehouses: There were
houses here. there were houses there.

899
01:46:05.951 --> 01:46:07.951
Herr Günsche.
I want to speak to the Führer.

900
01:46:09.952 --> 01:46:11.452
Please. I have to.

901
01:46:11.952 --> 01:46:14.452
Frau Goebbels. the Führer
doesn't want to be disturbed.

902
01:46:14.453 --> 01:46:17.452
Please. Günsche.
just for a moment.

903
01:46:17.952 --> 01:46:19.452
Please.

904
01:46:26.610 --> 01:46:29.110
Mein Führer. Frau Goebbels is here.

905
01:46:35.318 --> 01:46:36.818
What is it?

906
01:46:37.318 --> 01:46:40.818
Mein Führer. I beg you:
Leave Berlin.

907
01:46:41.818 --> 01:46:47.318
Don't leave us Führer.
What will become of us?

908
01:46:51.041 --> 01:46:58.041
Tomorrow. I'll be cursed by millions.
but that's how it is.

909
01:47:00.725 --> 01:47:02.725
Get up. Come.

910
01:47:05.225 --> 01:47:07.225
Come.

911
01:47:15.218 --> 01:47:17.718
Aunt Traudl. I like it
when it thunders.

912
01:47:18.218 --> 01:47:21.718
Why?
-Nothing can happen to us here.

913
01:47:22.218 --> 01:47:24.218
Can it?
-No.

914
01:47:33.334 --> 01:47:34.834
Gotcha.

915
01:47:56.904 --> 01:48:00.404
Reichsleiter. it's over.

916
01:48:18.495 --> 01:48:20.995
The Führer is dead.

917
01:48:36.105 --> 01:48:38.105
There's daddy.

918
01:48:49.099 --> 01:48:52.599
Are you crazy?
For that damned petrol of yours...

919
01:48:53.099 --> 01:48:55.099
Erich. shut up.

920
01:49:05.120 --> 01:49:06.620
Stand back.

921
01:49:19.522 --> 01:49:21.022
Come on. continue.

922
01:49:21.522 --> 01:49:23.022
Continue.

923
01:50:48.827 --> 01:50:51.827
No. don't.

924
01:50:53.055 --> 01:50:55.055
Let grandpa go.

925
01:51:01.144 --> 01:51:04.644
Order. Order.
We must have order.

926
01:51:05.644 --> 01:51:08.144
Order has to return.

927
01:51:21.878 --> 01:51:25.878
This way. We know the way.
You can trust us.

928
01:51:26.878 --> 01:51:28.378
Hurry.

929
01:51:34.621 --> 01:51:37.121
I was on the side of
the Red Beasts.

930
01:51:40.990 --> 01:51:42.990
I supported the Bolsheviks.

931
01:51:50.175 --> 01:51:51.675
Let's hope the Russians
got our message.

932
01:51:52.175 --> 01:51:54.675
We'll soon find out.
-Or not.

933
01:51:59.680 --> 01:52:02.680
What news do you have. General?

934
01:52:03.180 --> 01:52:08.180
Adolf Hitler and his wife
committed suicide in the bunker.

935
01:52:11.180 --> 01:52:15.180
The new government
authorised me...

936
01:52:17.180 --> 01:52:20.180
...to start peace talks...

937
01:52:20.680 --> 01:52:26.680
...between our countries. that both
suffered severe losses.

938
01:52:27.680 --> 01:52:32.180
General. if you were me.
would you make peace with you?

939
01:52:32.680 --> 01:52:36.680
My government will never accept
unconditional surrender.

940
01:52:39.180 --> 01:52:43.180
Given the situation.
you have no other choice.

941
01:52:46.180 --> 01:52:48.680
Surrender? Never.
That's shameful.

942
01:52:49.680 --> 01:52:51.680
Years ago. I conquered
Berlin on the Reds...

943
01:52:52.180 --> 01:52:56.180
...and I'll defend the city
to my dying day.

944
01:52:57.180 --> 01:52:59.680
In the short time I have
as Chancellor...

945
01:53:00.180 --> 01:53:04.180
...I'll never sign
a surrender treaty.

946
01:53:04.680 --> 01:53:07.680
It's for the sake of the people.
-The Führer's orders are final.

947
01:53:08.180 --> 01:53:11.680
This is crazy.
We have to start negotiations.

948
01:53:12.180 --> 01:53:15.181
I repeat. gentlemen:
I do not surrender.

949
01:53:16.181 --> 01:53:18.681
Send a message to Marshal Zhukov.
-Zhukov?

950
01:53:19.181 --> 01:53:21.681
What's happening?
-We're surrendering.

951
01:53:22.181 --> 01:53:25.181
Then I must kill you.
The Führer forbids any surrender.

952
01:53:44.471 --> 01:53:47.471
How long does it work?
-Around four hours.

953
01:54:23.109 --> 01:54:28.109
Children. the doctor has the medication
I told you about.

954
01:54:28.609 --> 01:54:31.109
It's a bit bitter.
but it will work.

955
01:54:32.609 --> 01:54:34.109
A sip for everybody.

956
01:54:35.609 --> 01:54:37.609
Who wants to go first?

957
01:54:40.109 --> 01:54:43.609
Heide. you're always so brave?

958
01:54:49.109 --> 01:54:50.609
Have another sip.

959
01:54:53.609 --> 01:54:55.609
See? That wasn't so bad.

960
01:55:00.549 --> 01:55:02.549
Well done.
Helmut.

961
01:55:05.549 --> 01:55:10.049
This medication makes sure you don't
get ill in this humid bunker.

962
01:55:10.549 --> 01:55:13.049
But it's not humid
in the bunker.

963
01:55:17.549 --> 01:55:19.049
Well done.

964
01:55:27.934 --> 01:55:29.434
Helga.

965
01:55:32.049 --> 01:55:33.049
I don't want to.

966
01:55:33.549 --> 01:55:37.988
What's that? Do you want to get sick?
-Please. mama. I don't want to drink it.

967
01:55:41.488 --> 01:55:45.488
Don't cry. baby.
That doesn't help.

968
01:55:45.988 --> 01:55:47.988
You have to drink the medicine.

969
01:55:51.488 --> 01:55:52.988
Helga.

970
01:55:58.488 --> 01:56:00.988
Come on. open your mouth.

971
01:56:21.434 --> 01:56:22.934
Goodnight. children.

972
01:56:33.258 --> 01:56:36.258
One day the lie will fall apart...

973
01:56:36.259 --> 01:56:39.258
...and there will be light
in the darkness.

974
01:56:40.258 --> 01:56:41.758
Please read that.

975
01:56:42.758 --> 01:56:47.258
One day the lie will fall apart
and there will be light in the darkness.

976
01:56:48.758 --> 01:56:51.758
Let's do it differently.
One day the lie will collapse...

977
01:56:52.258 --> 01:56:56.758
...and truth will triumph
once again.

978
01:56:57.258 --> 01:57:00.758
At that moment. we will
stand above everybody...

979
01:57:01.258 --> 01:57:03.258
...pure and...

980
01:57:06.258 --> 01:57:08.258
immaculate.

981
02:01:05.072 --> 02:01:08.072
We don't stand a chance.
-So what? I want to get away.

982
02:01:08.572 --> 02:01:10.072
How do we get
through the lines?

983
02:01:10.572 --> 02:01:13.072
Doesn't matter.
I'm not staying another minute.

984
02:01:13.572 --> 02:01:16.572
We'll die.
-It won't be that bad. surely.

985
02:01:17.572 --> 02:01:20.072
If we stay. the Russians
will get us for sure.

986
02:01:22.072 --> 02:01:23.072
All the best.

987
02:01:23.572 --> 02:01:25.572
Come. let's go.

988
02:02:50.756 --> 02:02:57.211
On 30 April 1945. the Führer
committed suicide...

989
02:02:57.212 --> 02:03:02.711
...and in doing so. he deserted
everybody who was loyal to him.

990
02:03:03.211 --> 02:03:08.211
You. German soldiers. were loyal to
the Führer and were prepared...

991
02:03:08.711 --> 02:03:14.711
...to continue the battle for Berlin.
although ammunition was in short supply...

992
02:03:15.211 --> 02:03:19.711
...and further resistance
was pointless.

993
02:03:20.211 --> 02:03:23.711
I hereby declare an
immediate cease-fire.

994
02:03:25.211 --> 02:03:27.711
Each hour you continue fighting...

995
02:03:28.211 --> 02:03:34.711
...prolongs the suffering of the people
of Berlin and of our wounded.

996
02:03:35.211 --> 02:03:38.711
In agreement with the supreme
command of the Soviet troops...

997
02:03:39.211 --> 02:03:44.711
...I order you to stop
fighting immediately.

998
02:03:45.211 --> 02:03:52.211
Weidling. former commander
of the Berlin defence area.

999
02:03:53.711 --> 02:03:55.711
A glass of water. please.

1000
02:04:58.724 --> 02:05:01.224
I don't need you anymore.

1001
02:05:04.224 --> 02:05:06.724
The game's over.

1002
02:06:11.707 --> 02:06:14.207
It's time.
-Don't you see what's going on here?

1003
02:06:14.707 --> 02:06:17.707
I insist that you help us.
as a doctor.

1004
02:06:18.707 --> 02:06:20.707
Alright. then.

1005
02:06:27.707 --> 02:06:32.207
Go. You did a lot.
Thank you.

1006
02:06:38.684 --> 02:06:44.525
Schädle. hurry. Come on.
-I'm not going anywhere anymore.

1007
02:06:47.025 --> 02:06:48.525
Come along.

1008
02:07:25.565 --> 02:07:28.065
Are you alright?
-Keep going.

1009
02:08:03.379 --> 02:08:06.879
Sturmmann Krüger and his group
defended the Wolf Bridge...

1010
02:08:07.379 --> 02:08:09.879
...and he receives the Iron Cross.

1011
02:08:10.379 --> 02:08:14.379
Sturmmann Wagner took out two
machine-gun nests...

1012
02:08:14.879 --> 02:08:17.879
...and therefore. receives
the Iron Cross.

1013
02:08:18.379 --> 02:08:21.879
Sturmmann Rauch has gotten
messages through the lines...

1014
02:08:22.379 --> 02:08:24.879
...and receives the Iron Cross.

1015
02:08:54.786 --> 02:08:56.786
The others are coming.

1016
02:09:03.156 --> 02:09:05.156
Take cover. Müller.

1017
02:09:23.988 --> 02:09:24.988
Who's that?

1018
02:09:32.333 --> 02:09:34.333
A German.

1019
02:09:39.727 --> 02:09:41.227
Herr Hewel?

1020
02:09:44.727 --> 02:09:46.727
Thank God. you're alive.

1021
02:09:48.727 --> 02:09:50.227
Where are the others?

1022
02:09:52.727 --> 02:09:56.727
I don't know. Frau Junge.
Somewhere. Maybe.

1023
02:09:57.227 --> 02:10:00.227
Most people from my group
must be dead.

1024
02:10:00.727 --> 02:10:03.227
I should never
have left that bunker.

1025
02:10:03.727 --> 02:10:08.227
I should have shot myself.
but I couldn't.

1026
02:10:10.227 --> 02:10:13.227
Eat something first.
There's always enough time to die.

1027
02:11:08.228 --> 02:11:10.728
You stay with the women.

1028
02:11:11.810 --> 02:11:13.310
Come along.

1029
02:11:25.334 --> 02:11:28.834
The Russians have surrounded us.
-What's going to happen to us?

1030
02:11:29.334 --> 02:11:31.834
Maybe you can get through.
You could try.

1031
02:11:32.334 --> 02:11:33.834
I'm not taking another step.

1032
02:11:34.834 --> 02:11:39.334
Think about it. The Russians
are after us.

1033
02:11:39.834 --> 02:11:44.834
As a woman. you might have a chance.
Try it.

1034
02:11:45.834 --> 02:11:47.334
Good luck.

1035
02:11:49.834 --> 02:11:53.834
When you walk past the Russians.
don't look them in the eyes.

1036
02:11:54.334 --> 02:11:57.834
Remember that well. All the best.

1037
02:12:06.493 --> 02:12:07.993
The Russians.

1038
02:12:20.060 --> 02:12:22.560
Gerda. let's go.
-You go.

1039
02:12:23.060 --> 02:12:26.060
I'm exhausted.
-Please.

1040
02:12:28.060 --> 02:12:32.060
I have to give it a try.
Don't be angry with me.

1041
02:12:36.060 --> 02:12:37.560
I'll be alright.

1042
02:12:50.137 --> 02:12:51.637
Herr Doktor.

1043
02:12:52.137 --> 02:12:56.637
My comrades want to surrender.
Can I join you?

1044
02:12:57.137 --> 02:13:00.637
The Führer's dead. Do you want
to continue the war on your own?

1045
02:13:01.137 --> 02:13:02.637
I'm obliged by my oath.

1046
02:13:03.137 --> 02:13:07.637
Then you'd better go
to the Brigadeführer.

1047
02:13:35.107 --> 02:13:36.607
The Russians are evacuating the square.
-So?

1048
02:13:37.607 --> 02:13:39.607
No opposition.
No shooting.

1049
02:13:40.106 --> 02:13:42.606
Then they'll be
here within the hour.

1050
02:13:43.106 --> 02:13:45.106
What shall we do?

1051
02:13:45.107 --> 02:13:49.606
We can't surrender.
-What exactly do you mean?

1052
02:13:50.106 --> 02:13:53.606
When the Russians come.
we'll empty our weapons on them.

1053
02:13:54.106 --> 02:13:57.606
The last bullets are for ourselves.
-That's radical.

1054
02:13:57.607 --> 02:14:02.606
Is this prestigious murder and suicide
our only option?

1055
02:14:03.106 --> 02:14:06.606
We're SS officers.
We can't survive the Führer.

1056
02:14:06.606 --> 02:14:09.606
Who agrees with me?

1057
02:15:52.763 --> 02:15:55.763
Come and sit down with me?
-Please.

1058
02:16:01.347 --> 02:16:06.347
Why do you want to continue living?
-And you? Why do you want to die?

1059
02:16:07.847 --> 02:16:09.847
See this?

1060
02:16:10.347 --> 02:16:13.347
The Führer gave it
to me personally.

1061
02:16:13.847 --> 02:16:17.347
As a last decoration?
-Maybe.

1062
02:16:17.847 --> 02:16:22.347
A goodbye present from Hitler.
I had to promise him something.

1063
02:16:22.348 --> 02:16:27.347
If the Russians get me.
I have to kill myself.

1064
02:16:29.347 --> 02:16:33.347
Did he make you promise that?
But why?

1065
02:16:33.847 --> 02:16:36.847
Maybe he didn't want
me to be forced...

1066
02:16:37.347 --> 02:16:39.347
...to say anything bad
about him.

1067
02:16:39.847 --> 02:16:43.847
But. as a diplomat.
you're under international protection.

1068
02:16:44.347 --> 02:16:47.847
Who will benefit
if you stick to your deal?

1069
02:16:48.347 --> 02:16:49.847
There they are.

1070
02:17:02.466 --> 02:17:03.966
Don't shoot. comrades.

1071
02:17:07.728 --> 02:17:12.228
We surrendered.
The war is over.

1072
02:17:13.228 --> 02:17:15.228
It's over.

1073
02:18:45.115 --> 02:18:48.115
Complete surrender took place
on 7 May 1945.

1074
02:18:50.115 --> 02:18:53.115
Hostilities were suspended
on 8 May.

1075
02:18:55.115 --> 02:18:58.615
The war took the lives of more
than 50 million people.

1076
02:19:00.115 --> 02:19:05.115
6 million Jews were killed
in German concentration camps.

1077
02:19:06.115 --> 02:19:10.615
Gerda Christian managed to escape
and avoid imprisonment.

1078
02:19:11.115 --> 02:19:14.115
She died in Düsseldorf
on 14 April 1997.

1079
02:19:14.615 --> 02:19:18.615
Dr. Schenck was released in 1953
by the Soviets.

1080
02:19:19.115 --> 02:19:22.615
He died in Aachen
on 21 December 1998.

1081
02:19:24.115 --> 02:19:26.615
Wilhelm Mohnke was released
by the Soviets in 1955.

1082
02:19:27.115 --> 02:19:31.115
He died in Damp. near Eckernförde.
on 6 August 2001.

1083
02:19:31.615 --> 02:19:37.615
Helmut Weidling died in
captivity. in 1955.

1084
02:19:38.115 --> 02:19:43.115
Werner Haase was arrested
in the bunker. by the Red Army.

1085
02:19:43.615 --> 02:19:46.615
He died in captivity.
in 1945.

1086
02:19:47.115 --> 02:19:50.115
Otto Günsche was arrested
by the Soviets.

1087
02:19:50.615 --> 02:19:54.615
He was released in 1956 and
died in Lohmar. in 2003.

1088
02:19:55.115 --> 02:19:59.615
Hanna Reitsch survived the war
and would break many flying records.

1089
02:20:00.115 --> 02:20:02.615
She died on 28 August 1979.

1090
02:20:03.115 --> 02:20:08.115
Robert Ritter von Greim committed
suicide on 24 May 1945.

1091
02:20:08.615 --> 02:20:11.115
Linge and Hentschel were
arrested by the Soviets.

1092
02:20:11.615 --> 02:20:13.615
Linge was released in 1955 and
died in 1980.

1093
02:20:14.615 --> 02:20:17.615
Hentschel was released in 1949 and
died in 1982.

1094
02:20:18.115 --> 02:20:24.115
Constanze Manziarly disappeared
without a trace. during her flight.

1095
02:20:24.615 --> 02:20:27.615
Albert Speer was arrested
in Flensburg. in 1945.

1096
02:20:28.115 --> 02:20:30.615
He was sentenced to
20 years. in Nuremberg.

1097
02:20:31.115 --> 02:20:33.615
He was released in 1966 and
died in London. in 1981.

1098
02:20:34.615 --> 02:20:40.615
Keitel and Jodl were sentenced to
death in Nuremberg and executed.

1099
02:20:41.615 --> 02:20:43.615
Hermann Göring was
sentenced to death.

1100
02:20:44.615 --> 02:20:47.615
He committed suicide in his cell.
shortly before his execution.

1101
02:20:48.115 --> 02:20:52.615
Heinrich Himmler tried to escape
using a false name.

1102
02:20:53.115 --> 02:20:56.115
After he was found out.
he committed suicide.

1103
02:20:56.615 --> 02:21:01.115
Martin Bormann and Ludwig
Stumpfegger committed suicide...

1104
02:21:01.615 --> 02:21:04.615
...on 2 May 1945.
near the Lehrter Bahnhof.

1105
02:21:05.615 --> 02:21:09.615
Rochus Misch was released
by the Soviets in 1955.

1106
02:21:10.115 --> 02:21:12.115
He still lives in Berlin.

1107
02:21:12.615 --> 02:21:15.115
Traudl Junge was classified
as a 'young follower'.

1108
02:21:15.615 --> 02:21:18.615
She worked as a secretary and lived
in Munich. until her death in 2002.

1109
02:21:19.115 --> 02:21:24.115
All the horror I heard about during
the Nuremberg trial...

1110
02:21:24.116 --> 02:21:30.616
...the 6 million Jews. dissidents
or people of another race...

1111
02:21:31.116 --> 02:21:36.616
...who died. shocked me deeply.

1112
02:21:37.616 --> 02:21:42.116
But I hadn't made the connection
with my own past yet.

1113
02:21:43.116 --> 02:21:47.616
I reassured myself by thinking
I wasn't personally guilty of it.

1114
02:21:48.116 --> 02:21:53.116
And that I hadn't known
about the sheer size of it.

1115
02:21:53.616 --> 02:21:59.616
But one day. I walked
past a commemorative plaque...

1116
02:22:00.116 --> 02:22:03.616
...for Sophie Scholl.
here in the Franz-Joseph-Strasse.

1117
02:22:04.616 --> 02:22:07.116
I saw that she was my age...

1118
02:22:07.616 --> 02:22:13.116
...and that she was executed in
the year I joined Hitler.

1119
02:22:13.616 --> 02:22:18.616
And only then did I realise...

1120
02:22:19.616 --> 02:22:22.116
that youth is no excuse.

1121
02:22:22.616 --> 02:22:28.616
And that it might have been
possible to find out the truth.

1122
02:24:58.270 --> 02:25:01.270
DOWNFALL
